node.title: Victoria records 1,252 new local COVID-19 cases and five deaths
node.alt: Crowds in Melbourne's Bourke Street Mall
node.description: There are now 11,257 active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 499 people have died during the state's current Delta outbreak.
node.content: ["Victoria has recorded 1,252\u00a0new local COVID-19 cases and five\u00a0deaths.", "There are now 11,257\u00a0active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 499\u00a0people have died during the state's current Delta outbreak.\u00a0", "There are 299\u00a0people in hospital with COVID-19, of whom 42\u00a0are in intensive care and 22\u00a0are on a ventilator.", "The health department said a further 48\u00a0people were in intensive care but their COVID-19 infections were no longer considered active.", "The new cases were detected from 57,292\u00a0test results received yesterday.", "There were 4,938\u00a0doses of vaccine administered at state-run sites yesterday, and more vaccinations at GP clinics and other venues.", "Victoria has now fully vaccinated 90 per cent of its population aged 12 and older.", "More to come."]
